definitions.definition: A cultural region , historical province , and peninsula in northwest France . [from 15th c.]
An administrative region of northwest France , including most of the historic region of Brittany. [from 20th c.]
( obsolete , chiefly poetic ) The British Isles . [15th–19th c.]
A female given name transferred from the place name, of 1980s and 1990s American usage .
